raw_data.title: Analyst I
raw_data.description: A person with experience in scientific or engineering studies who has developed good technical analysis skills and is able to perform research tasks with a minimum level of supervision, contributing significantly to both the technical effort and presentation of results to the customer. This is a well-educated engineer or scientist, with a Masters degree and 3 years experience, or a Bachelor of Science or Arts degree and 5 years experience, or a total of 10 years experience in their technical specialty. Responsibilities include directing technical projects involving several other staff members, and/or providing guidance on implementation of requirements in their specialty area

raw_data.title: Analyst II
raw_data.description: A person with experience in scientific or engineering studies who has developed good technical analysis skills and is able to perform research tasks with a minimum level of supervision, contributing significantly to both the technical effort and presentation of results to the customer. This is a well-educated engineer or scientist, with a Master’s degree, or a Bachelor of Science or Arts degree and 3 years experience, or a total of 10 years experience in their technical specialty. Shares responsibility for organizing and planning the technical effort.

raw_data.title: Junior Analyst I
raw_data.description: A person who applies scientific or engineering training to technical studies or research, with a Bachelor of Science or Arts degree

raw_data.title: Senior Analyst I
raw_data.description: A person with considerable experience in scientific or engineering studies, who has demonstrated superior technical analysis capabilities and accepted responsibility for directing projects of significant technical depth and complexity. This is a highly educated engineer or scientist, capable of sound independent judgment, with one or more advanced degrees and 8 years experience, or a Bachelor of Science or Arts degree and 10 years applicable experience. Responsibilities include interaction with customers, and providing guidance on implementation of requirements in their specialty area

raw_data.title: Senior Analyst II
raw_data.description: A person with considerable experience in scientific or engineering studies, who has demonstrated superior technical analysis capabilities and accepted responsibility for directing technical projects involving several other staff members. This is a highly educated engineer or scientist, capable of sound independent judgment, with a one or more advanced degrees and 6 years experience, or a Bachelor of Science or Arts degree and 8 years experience, or a total of 20 years experience in their technical specialty. Responsible for interaction with customers, including coordination, review, and delivery of technical products

raw_data.title: Senior Scientist I
raw_data.description: A person of extensive experience in professional scientific or engineering studies, with a national reputation or widely recognized excellence in their field of expertise. This is a highly educated engineer or scientist with one or more advanced degrees and 30 years applicable experience, directing the activities of a research and development organization. Responsibilities include reviewing and approving the implementation of requirements across the enterprise.

raw_data.title: Senior Scientist II
raw_data.description: A person of extensive experience in professional scientific or engineering studies, with a national reputation or widely recognized excellence in their field of expertise. This is a highly educated engineer or scientist with one or more advanced degrees and 15 years experience, or a Bachelor of Science or Arts degree and 20 years applicable experience, capable of performing independent research. Responsibilities include directing research projects of significant technical depth and complexity, and leading the implementation of requirements in their area of responsibility.

raw_data.title: Senior Staff Analyst I
raw_data.description: A person with lengthy experience in scientific or engineering studies, who has by their past accomplishments achieved a high level of expertise and accepted significant responsibility for both technical performance and project execution. This is a highly educated engineer or scientist with one or more advanced degrees and 12 years experience, or a Bachelor of Science or Arts degree and 15 years applicable experience, and has demonstrated superior independent judgment. Responsibilities include leading multi-disciplinary technical projects and directing the implementation of requirements in their specialty area

raw_data.title: Senior Staff Analyst II
raw_data.description: A person with lengthy experience in scientific or engineering studies, who has by their past accomplishments achieved a high level of expertise and accepted significant responsibility for both technical performance and project execution. This is a highly educated engineer or scientist with one or more advanced degrees and 8 years experience, or a Bachelor of Science or Arts degree and 10 years applicable experience, and has demonstrated superior independent judgment. Responsibilities include directing projects of significant technical depth and complexity

raw_data.title: Junior Analyst I
raw_data.description: A person responsible for support of technical projects, with a Masters degree and 6 years experience, or a Bachelor of Science or Arts degree and 8 years experience, or a total of 12 years experience in their support specialty. Includes such personnel as administrative assistants, IT, facilities, subcontracts administrators, security specialists and technicians. Manages an administrative or operations area, and/or provides guidance on implementation of requirements, in their support area.

raw_data.title: Technical Support I
raw_data.description: A person responsible for support of technical projects, with a Bachelor of Science or Arts degree and 3 years experience, or an Associate degree and 5 years experience, or a total of 7 years experience in their support specialty. Includes such personnel as administrative assistants, IT, facilities, subcontracts administrators, security specialists and technicians.

raw_data.title: Technical Support II
raw_data.description: A person responsible for support of technical projects, with a Bachelor of Science or Arts degree or an Associate degree. Includes such personnel as administrative assistants, IT, facilities, subcontracts administrators, security specialists and technicians
